Cell["\<\
Notice how there is several cases where the tail becomes flat, or there is no \
solution to the problem. This is because a single-jointed tail can only \
rotate so much. To get around this, I developed a third model for a \
multi-jointed tail:\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.992513170336986*^9, 3.9925132081499968`*^9}, {
  3.992597903948073*^9, 3.9925979196538887`*^9}, {3.992602717781084*^9, 
  3.9926027190287704`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"52a58416-ac84-4620-8106-\
34f428c17f09"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Model V3 - Multi-Jointed Self-Balancing Tail", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.992549167163578*^9},ExpressionUUID->"36bd5569-c204-41ca-8366-\
1726f2bf7789"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "With model V2 developed, which has a joint which can rotate freely to \
counterbalance ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "lean"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "396060b2-a383-4e1f-87a9-49e62f41f5b8"],
 ", the tail was nearly fully modeled. However, once again, in nature, \
monkeys and mammals in general have multi-jointed tails ranging from 11 to 49 \
caudal vertebrae (bones). To simulate this, I created an algorithm that can \
take any number of joints, a given segment length and weight, and a ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "lean"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "49b5ce40-16bf-4a52-894c-69b92d0bf42c"],
 ", and computes the angles of the vertebrae. "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9924182846744537`*^9, 3.992418319051136*^9}, {
   3.992418350578918*^9, 3.992418412636354*^9}, {3.992418475915766*^9, 
   3.992418615624667*^9}, {3.992418649433734*^9, 3.992418668332036*^9}, {
   3.9924187075300007`*^9, 3.9924188824505053`*^9}, 3.992420983827877*^9, {
   3.99242117495825*^9, 3.992421174958345*^9}, {3.992421292418934*^9, 
   3.992421328360664*^9}, {3.992421403622285*^9, 3.9924214478462667`*^9}, {
   3.992421559880987*^9, 3.992421592079218*^9}, {3.992421688029912*^9, 
   3.992421741583941*^9}, {3.9924218192142973`*^9, 3.992421819214427*^9}, 
   3.99242203718818*^9, {3.9924222545826607`*^9, 3.992422277626573*^9}, {
   3.9924234221371117`*^9, 3.992423443997818*^9}, {3.992423536113207*^9, 
   3.992423682082191*^9}, {3.9924238705781116`*^9, 3.99242387668334*^9}, {
   3.992425049548092*^9, 3.992425057403997*^9}, {3.9924285994951973`*^9, 
   3.992428662570973*^9}, {3.992428850322914*^9, 3.992428908887649*^9}, {
   3.9924290185375557`*^9, 3.992429084659481*^9}, {3.992429220944626*^9, 
   3.9924292334484262`*^9}, {3.992429283904768*^9, 3.992429285229557*^9}, {
   3.992442128896966*^9, 3.992442142513588*^9}, {3.992444015131404*^9, 
   3.992444019555094*^9}, {3.992445700084337*^9, 3.992445706941646*^9}, {
   3.992591350453874*^9, 3.9925913686350813`*^9}, {3.9925928760958633`*^9, 
   3.9925928766980133`*^9}, {3.9925938505548162`*^9, 3.992593885530525*^9}, {
   3.992597923104145*^9, 3.99259803477374*^9}, 3.992601620660717*^9, 
   3.992602747969656*^9},ExpressionUUID->"7ce9c8e8-2a18-4875-8353-\
89e5cbdf2481"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "To do this, I redefined the naming system for my variables. V1 and V2 have \
six points each, each titled ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["p", "n"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "211857a0-4927-b843-9234-c9df960a17f8"],
 ", but approaching adding more and more points as well as midpoints/center \
of masses computationally will get unnecessary and convoluted. Thus, for this \
final model, I named the pivot points with the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["p", "n"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "135b4d34-62da-d841-9fac-ca47509acf17"],
 " system, and named the midpoints/center of masses with the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["m", "n"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "c863f73f-bc4e-7045-8ce4-b561b90b7a87"],
 " system. Because the n applies for the tail and only the tail, but I still \
had pivots and center of masses elsewhere, I named the origin and head points \
with these special exceptions:"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9924182846744537`*^9, 3.992418319051136*^9}, {
   3.992418350578918*^9, 3.992418412636354*^9}, {3.992418475915766*^9, 
   3.992418615624667*^9}, {3.992418649433734*^9, 3.992418668332036*^9}, {
   3.9924187075300007`*^9, 3.9924188824505053`*^9}, 3.992420983827877*^9, {
   3.99242117495825*^9, 3.992421174958345*^9}, {3.992421292418934*^9, 
   3.992421328360664*^9}, {3.992421403622285*^9, 3.9924214478462667`*^9}, {
   3.992421559880987*^9, 3.992421592079218*^9}, {3.992421688029912*^9, 
   3.992421741583941*^9}, {3.9924218192142973`*^9, 3.992421819214427*^9}, 
   3.99242203718818*^9, {3.9924222545826607`*^9, 3.992422277626573*^9}, {
   3.9924234221371117`*^9, 3.992423443997818*^9}, {3.992423536113207*^9, 
   3.992423682082191*^9}, {3.9924238705781116`*^9, 3.99242387668334*^9}, {
   3.992425049548092*^9, 3.992425057403997*^9}, {3.9924285994951973`*^9, 
   3.992428662570973*^9}, {3.992428850322914*^9, 3.992428908887649*^9}, {
   3.9924290185375557`*^9, 3.992429084659481*^9}, {3.992429220944626*^9, 
   3.9924292334484262`*^9}, {3.992429283904768*^9, 3.992429285229557*^9}, {
   3.992442128896966*^9, 3.992442142513588*^9}, {3.992444015131404*^9, 
   3.992444019555094*^9}, {3.992445700084337*^9, 3.992445706941646*^9}, {
   3.992591350453874*^9, 3.9925913686350813`*^9}, {3.9925928760958633`*^9, 
   3.9925928766980133`*^9}, {3.9925938505548162`*^9, 3.992593885530525*^9}, {
   3.992597923104145*^9, 3.99259803477374*^9}, 
   3.992601620660717*^9},ExpressionUUID->"429e982b-5db2-ba4b-8774-\
34f216f3830b"],

