Cell[TextData[{
 "With these points defined, I began computing. Each of these joints must be \
able to rotate. In the previous Model V2, I defined a new angle, ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "adj"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "5c4ad72b-68b9-4945-a5b9-88a0d2d17a0c"],
 ", such that it could rotate. Because each n-numbered joint is rotating, \
however, I now need n number of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "adj"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "e05e5d47-ef03-445d-8199-23eb9c9cfbf8"],
 " angles, each one named appropriately as ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", 
    RowBox[{"adj", " ", "n"}]], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "3ed45be1-23ee-4910-a2a8-ed2cd5cc2f33"],
 ". In the above three-joint, the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "adj"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "55afe090-e7a9-412b-9178-340f12524433"],
 " angles were defined as the following:"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9924182846744537`*^9, 3.992418319051136*^9}, {
   3.992418350578918*^9, 3.992418412636354*^9}, {3.992418475915766*^9, 
