Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Conclusion", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.992549335859342*^9, 3.992549336865078*^9}, 
   3.992607474124756*^9},ExpressionUUID->"c1c1283e-947c-43d2-b3e7-\
303a7563bd01"],

Cell["\<\
The development process of this model and algorithm demonstrate the \
progression from studying a biological phenomenon (prehensile tails), \
calculating how they would work mathematically, and then implementing them in \
an interactive simulation. The model\[CloseCurlyQuote]s iterative versions in \
the form of a V1, V2, and V3 showcase an evolution of complexity, creating a \
greater foundation for the eventual algorithm. In the end, the model holds \
strong applications in robotics and understanding how organisms naturally \
balance themselves with tails. Researchers can now specify design constraints \
and the model will output estimated results for them to test and iterate on.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9925493383251257`*^9, 3.992549338862523*^9}, {
   3.992558779635724*^9, 3.992558802484908*^9}, {3.9925588364480267`*^9, 
   3.9925588377093363`*^9}, {3.992558910463369*^9, 3.992559003867692*^9}, {
   3.992559051844049*^9, 3.9925591755875387`*^9}, {3.992559334112504*^9, 
   3.992559388204668*^9}, {3.992560774085911*^9, 3.9925610964327297`*^9}, 
   3.9925637309894342`*^9, {3.9925638717250566`*^9, 3.992563873999549*^9}, {
   3.992563953551787*^9, 3.992564152735304*^9}, {3.992564518787458*^9, 
   3.9925645239862747`*^9}, {3.992607511557249*^9, 
   3.992607551141655*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"166583a8-6fc5-48ad-90d6-\
7495da2bfaca"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Despite the successes, the model has shortcomings. Firstly, the model is in \
2-D. If the algorithm was ever implemented into real robotics, it would have \
to be modified to work around in a 3-D space. This 2-D limit is especially \
demonstrated and problematic when the mass leans backwards\[LongDash]when ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "lean"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "aacc193e-3d54-ce48-8c99-cbb5df081979"],
 " is negative. Sometimes instead of wrapping around, the tail will emerge \
from the front instead of the back, also known as flipping. The tail may \
appear to pass through the body as well. The visual simulation of the model \
also shows that the model sometimes creates angles which fold in on \
themselves, or have angles too sharp for a real prehensile tail."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9925493383251257`*^9, 3.992549338862523*^9}, {
   3.992558779635724*^9, 3.992558802484908*^9}, {3.9925588364480267`*^9, 
   3.9925588377093363`*^9}, {3.992558910463369*^9, 3.992559003867692*^9}, {
   3.992559051844049*^9, 3.9925591755875387`*^9}, {3.992559334112504*^9, 
   3.992559388204668*^9}, {3.992560774085911*^9, 3.9925610964327297`*^9}, 
   3.9925637309894342`*^9, {3.9925638717250566`*^9, 3.992563873999549*^9}, {
   3.992563953551787*^9, 3.992564152735304*^9}, {3.992564518787458*^9, 
   3.9925645239862747`*^9}, {3.992607511557249*^9, 3.9926075472500362`*^9}, {
   3.9926075838181095`*^9, 
   3.992607746915682*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"cf917dbf-a3ab-1d42-9037-\
e78f60c36f63"],

Cell["\<\
In general, the model and algorithm are mostly successful, new, and \
innovative first steps to approaching new robotic tail problems; however, in \
order to be fully implemented, true 3-D spatial awareness, as well as better \
angle constraints must be added to prevent solutions with impossible \
real-world implementation.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9925493383251257`*^9, 3.992549338862523*^9}, {
   3.992558779635724*^9, 3.992558802484908*^9}, {3.9925588364480267`*^9, 
   3.9925588377093363`*^9}, {3.992558910463369*^9, 3.992559003867692*^9}, {
   3.992559051844049*^9, 3.9925591755875387`*^9}, {3.992559334112504*^9, 
   3.992559388204668*^9}, {3.992560774085911*^9, 3.9925610964327297`*^9}, 
   3.9925637309894342`*^9, {3.9925638717250566`*^9, 3.992563873999549*^9}, {
   3.992563953551787*^9, 3.992564152735304*^9}, {3.992564518787458*^9, 
   3.9925645239862747`*^9}, {3.992607511557249*^9, 3.9926075472500362`*^9}, {
   3.9926075838181095`*^9, 3.992607743295143*^9}, {3.992607777450289*^9, 
   3.9926078024627705`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"3c82f319-8785-e047-a167-\
95ecbe02f6b2"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Future Directions", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.992549383513165*^9, 
  3.99254938612042*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"28d90bb3-41f1-4caa-9539-\
471d8aea7daa"],

Cell["\<\
Due to the model\[CloseCurlyQuote]s minor flaws listed above, additional work \
on the parameters and math can be done. Any future investigations could \
answer the research questions of how the algorithm can be optimized, how it \
can be implemented in 3-D spaces, and how more realistic and \
\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]natural\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] curves can be \
implemented. \
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9925493975436287`*^9, 3.9925493977732153`*^9}, {
   3.9925643642661467`*^9, 3.99256436926619*^9}, {3.992564399702474*^9, 
   3.9925644338493156`*^9}, {3.992564510144314*^9, 3.9925645295723877`*^9}, {
   3.992564576269917*^9, 3.99256500545851*^9}, {3.9925651012682962`*^9, 
   3.992565376946836*^9}, 3.992607827497017*^9, 3.99260786347456*^9, {
   3.992607908311056*^9, 
   3.992607992697939*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"c276f46f-8cee-4786-a933-\
520a07c7687b"],

Cell["\<\
Adopting closer procedures to past studies may also help resolve uncertainty \
in the model. For instance, the math could more closely follow the equations \
set up by Fu et al. (2024), which involve differential equations and calculus \
compared to mine which only uses trigonometry.  Fu et al. (2024) also modeled \
the single-jointed tail in a 3-D space with roll, pitch, and yaw, which \
future research should aim to do.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9925493975436287`*^9, 3.9925493977732153`*^9}, {
   3.9925643642661467`*^9, 3.99256436926619*^9}, {3.992564399702474*^9, 
   3.9925644338493156`*^9}, {3.992564510144314*^9, 3.9925645295723877`*^9}, {
   3.992564576269917*^9, 3.99256500545851*^9}, {3.9925651012682962`*^9, 
   3.992565376946836*^9}, 3.992607827497017*^9, 3.99260786347456*^9, {
   3.992607908311056*^9, 
   3.992607993645439*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"a8a1edf9-33e7-8146-bbf8-\
c22dbb10e0fc"],

Cell["\<\
Likewise in terms of alternate models, feedback controllers and something \
similar to an inverse pendulum mechanism could be explored to model the tail. \
PD control was utilized by Libby et al. (2012), and alternatives such as PD \
LQR are often used by inverse pendulum mechanisms in Wolfram. Libby et al. \
(2012) also built a physical model of the robot they were modeling. The Arque \
tail by Junichi Nabeshima et al. (2019) is a physical model too. Thus, \
building a physical model of a tail using my algorithm would explore its \
potential successes, shortcomings, and interactions in 3-D spaces.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9925493975436287`*^9, 3.9925493977732153`*^9}, {
   3.9925643642661467`*^9, 3.99256436926619*^9}, {3.992564399702474*^9, 
   3.9925644338493156`*^9}, {3.992564510144314*^9, 3.9925645295723877`*^9}, {
   3.992564576269917*^9, 3.99256500545851*^9}, {3.9925651012682962`*^9, 
   3.992565376946836*^9}, 3.992607827497017*^9, 3.99260786347456*^9, {
   3.992607908311056*^9, 
   3.992607994745592*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"d3943061-c638-154b-9652-\
520f7bfa8aed"],

Cell["\<\
Finally, adapting my tail\[CloseCurlyQuote]s physics from balance, which uses \
center of masses and torque, to something more complex, such as hanging, \
swinging, or grasping, would provide a more comprehensive idea of a monkey\
\[CloseCurlyQuote]s biomechanics. By expanding to different aspects of \
prehensile tails, the model will become more general purpose and accurate to \
a monkey.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9925493975436287`*^9, 3.9925493977732153`*^9}, {
   3.9925643642661467`*^9, 3.99256436926619*^9}, {3.992564399702474*^9, 
   3.9925644338493156`*^9}, {3.992564510144314*^9, 3.9925645295723877`*^9}, {
   3.992564576269917*^9, 3.99256500545851*^9}, {3.9925651012682962`*^9, 
   3.992565376946836*^9}, 3.992607827497017*^9, 3.99260786347456*^9, {
   3.992607908311056*^9, 
   3.9926080118957176`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"4834726d-0114-9244-90d1-\
487e1e27fa19"],

Cell["\<\
Overall, through addressing performance issues directly through new ideas and \
approaches from other researchers, more realistic and applicable models may \
be created.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9925493975436287`*^9, 3.9925493977732153`*^9}, {
   3.9925643642661467`*^9, 3.99256436926619*^9}, {3.992564399702474*^9, 
